<p align="left"><b><a href="nov05.htm">NOVEMBER 2005 :</a></b> <b>Mr Key has a 
  lie down and adds not a jot to the site. </b></p>
<p align="left"><b><a href="oct05.htm">OCTOBER 2005 :</a> Learn everything you 
  need to know about the shelling of peas, the Magic Mountain, Ayn Rand's funeral 
  song, English composer William Hurlstone, and the giant terrifying mountains 
  of Tantarabim.</b></p>
<p align="left"><b><a href="sep05.htm">SEPTEMBER 2005 :</a> Zeigler and Locke, 
  wisps and clumps, the magnificent Ukrainian bee counting game, and a picture 
  of a stormy petrel are among this month's undoubted highlights.</b></p>
<p align="left"><b><a href="aug05.htm">AUGUST 2005 :</a> Read all about hendiadys 
  in Mudchute, Reginald Bosanquet, <i>The Bog People</i> by P V Glob, the smashed 
  god, a dream about Roy Kinnear, cows, blubber, tallow and tin... and not to 
